article.headline: UCF 80, Presbyterian 53
article.story: ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) -- Jermaine Taylor scored 18 of his game-high 22 points in the first half and had six rebounds to lead UCF in an 80-53 win over Presbyterian on Wednesday night. Pierre Miller had a 3-pointer for Presbyterian with 18:09 in the game to cut UCF's lead to 51-40. The Knights responded with a 12-2 run to push their lead to 63-42. UCF (4-2) shot 61 percent from the floor (33 of 55). Tony Davis finished with 14 points for UCF, including 12 in the second half. Kenrick Zondervan scored 13 points and pulled down 15 rebounds, while Chip Cartwright finished with eight assists. Bryan Bostic led Presbyterian (0-8) with 11 points and seven rebounds. Josh Johnson finished with 10 points. UCF trailed only once, 5-2, after a three-pointer by Bostic. The Knights went on a 10-1 run to take a 12-6 lead and cruised from there. The Knights led by as many as 14 points in the first half and took a 49-37 lead into the locker room at halftime.
